      "review_summary": "The PR imports the existing memory QMD session transcript predicate into `extensions/memory-core/src/cli.runtime.ts` and uses it for `/memory status` session file counts instead of raw `.jsonl` suffix matching.\n\nPR surface: Source +1. Total +1 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. Current main counts the status denominator with a raw `.jsonl` suffix while the indexer uses the usage-counted helper, and the canonical issue provides fleet reproduction evidence; I did not run a live CLI repro in this read-only review.",
